# Authentication Project

## Description

This project showcases a practical implementation of user authentication using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, and Bootstrap. It interacts with the [Reqres](https://reqres.in/) API, simulating user registration and generating an authentication token upon successful signup.

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- [Git](https://git-scm.com/)
- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)

### Installation

1. **Clone the repository:**
    ```bash
    git clone https://github.com/abdallahawad3/Authentication-practice.git
    ```

3. **Install dependencies:**
    ```bash
    npm install
    ```
    *Note: The `node_modules` folder is listed in the `.gitignore` file to avoid pushing it to the repository. The project relies on the `package-lock.json` and `package.json` files to manage dependencies.*

